quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  5,20,"When Moses said to his people, 'O my people, remember God's blessings upon you, when He placed prophets among you, and made you kings, and gave you what He never gave any other people"
  5,21,"O my people, enter the Holy Land which God has assigned for you, and do not turn back, lest you return as losers"
  5,22,"They said, 'O Moses, there are tyrannical people in it; we will not enter it until they leave it. If they leave it, we will be entering"
  5,23,"Two men of those who feared, but whom God had blessed, said, 'Go at them by the gate; and when you have entered it, you will prevail. And put your trust in God, if you are believers"
  5,24,"They said, 'O Moses, we will not enter it, ever, as long as they are in it. So go ahead, you and your Lord, and fight. We are staying right here"
  5,25,"He said, 'My Lord! I have control only over myself and my brother, so separate between us and between the wicked people"
  5,26,"He said, 'It is forbidden for them for forty years. They will wander aimlessly in the land. So do not grieve over the defiant people"